description.plain:
Sergio Giavanni Kitchens (born June 14, 1993), better known by his stage name Gunna, is an American rapper from College Park, Georgia. Known for his melodic flows, he was introduced to  Young Thug through friend and mentor Keith Troup and subsequently signed to Thug’s record label, Young Stoner Life Records.

Gunna dropped his debut mixtape Drip Season in October of 2016. He released Drip Season 2 the following year and in 2018 ended the trilogy on a high-note with Drip Season 3,  which peaked at #55 on the Billboard 200.

In October of 2018, Gunna released Drip Harder, a collaborative mixtape with Lil Baby. The two continue to work together frequently and have showcased their chemistry on tracks such as Gunna’s “Sold Out Dates“ and “Oh Okay.“ Drip Harder’s hit track and lead single, “Drip Too Hard,“ peaked at #4 on the Billboard Hot 100.

Gunna followed up on the success of Drip Harder with his debut studio album, Drip or Drown 2, in February of 2019. His sophomore album, WUNNA dropped in May of 2020.

description.plain:
Gunna and Lil Baby team up once again on “Sold Out Dates.” On the song, they rap about their successful careers, noting how they are selling out concert venues and making money everyday. The song features a smooth, string-based instrumental from Turbo and Ghetto Guitar.

“Sold Out Dates” was originally leaked online. Following the leak, Gunna officially released the song on his YouTube channel. For months, fans (incorrectly) assumed it was the lead single from Drip Harder, Baby and Gunna’s debut collaborative album. However, the song will remain a standalone single.

“Baby Birkin” is one of two songs on the album whose title is inspired by a designer brand, the other being “Richard Millie Plain”, after the Swiss watch brand Richard Mille. Birkin is a luxury brand of leather bags by Hermes.

On the track, Gunna reflects on his newly found money and success. With this, he can afford his future daughter a baby Birkin bag. The bags are known to cost between $12,000 up to over $200,000.



The song also features topics on women and subtle references to gun violence.

description.plain:
“Car Sick” sees Gunna teaming up with NAV and Metro Boomin.
The featured artists both produced this track and is one of the standout tracks from Drip Season 3.

This track details the rich rapper lifestyle of Gunna and NAV. Most of their lines can be interpreted as a celebration to obtaining expensive clothing, jewelry or “drip,” but they both also drop retrospective bars about the envy that they arouse.

Gunna and NAV’s first verses go back-to-back, which in musical terms, is called a verse-to-verse flow. The chorus is split in half with NAV rapping the first half and Gunna rapping the second half.

description.plain:
On “TOP FLOOR,” Gunna reunites with Travis Scott for a melodic track about their expensive lifestyles, specifically their clothing, cars, and jewelry.

The trumpet pattern on this track is reminiscent of the one on Young Thug’s August 2019 track, “Hot,” which prominently features Gunna. Travis later featured on the official remix in October 2019. Both “Hot” and “TOP FLOOR” are produced by Wheezy, so this is somewhat a quasi-sequel.

On December 26, 2019, Travis and his DJ, Chase B, previewed “TOP FLOOR” while on Instagram Live. It’s unknown if this was originally Travis’ song, but the live stream in which it was teased occurred a day before Travis and his record label, Cactus Jack, released their compilation project, JACKBOYS. Travis only debuted his verse and chorus, so Gunna likely added his contributions to the track at a later date.

Gunna then teased a final snippet of the song with unheard Thug vocals on his 27th birthday in his Instagram Story. After over a year since it was first teased, Gunna finally released the track on the WUNNA Deluxe album.

description.plain:
“YSL” is a Playboi Carti-assisted song from Gunna’s second mixtape, Drip Season 2.

YSL is an acronym for both, luxury French cosmetics and fashion Brand, Yves Saint Laurent and the label Gunna’s signed to, YSL (Young Stoner Life) Records, a label ran by fellow Atlanta rapper, Young Thug.



Gunna with an Yves Saint Laurent T-shirt and YSL chain.

On the song, Gunna and Carti rap about buying and flaunting Yves Saint Laurent, while also paying homage to YSL Records. Gunna also documents the changes his life has undergone after signing and becoming rich.

“YSL” was also featured on Frank Ocean’s “Blonded” 97.8 FM" Radio on the video game Grand Theft Auto V.

On “Valentino,” Philadelphia rapper Lil Uzi Vert and Atlanta rapper Gunna team up on a boastful ode to designer brands. “Valentino” is an expensive designer clothing brand that originated in Italy.

Gunna and Lil Uzi Vert have collaborated three times before, on 2017’s “Marvelous Day,” 2018’s “At The Hotel” and 2018’s “Life Goes On”.

“Derek Fisher” is Gunna’s semi-homage to one of basketball’s greats, the titular Derek Fisher. Interestingly, this is the second song on Drip or Drown 2 with a basketball player’s name as the title, the first being “Yao Ming”.

Lyrically, the track is about Gunna’s love for guns, cars, and women, while also mourning some of his homies who have passed.

The title is a reference to retired basketball player and hall of famer Yao Ming who played for the Shanghai Sharks and Houston Rockets during his career. He stands at 7’6” and was the tallest player in the NBA until his departure.



Gunna juxtaposes his money to Yao Ming’s height and discusses themes of wealth, drip, drugs and women.
